{
  "name": "Nhimbaloth - Major Curse",
  "type": "effect",
  "effects": [],
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "gm": "<p><em>What I felt was no ordinary ghostly fear. It was infinitely greater, stranger, and seemed to arise from some dim ancestral sense of terror more profoundly disturbing than anything I had known or dreamed of. To be carried over the border and deprived of what I called \"my life,\" yet by mental, not physical, processes! A radical alteration, a complete change, a horrible loss of oneself by substitution—the emptiest of deaths.</em></p>",
      "value": "<section class=\"statblock secret\" id=\"secret-pQnRODKmTYc6SY3Q\"><p><strong>Saving Throw</strong> @Check[type:will|dc:33|showDC:gml|traits:curse,auditory,illusion,magical,mental,visual]{Will save}</p><p><strong>Timeline</strong> Abomination Vaults Book 3</p><p><strong>Suggested Triggers</strong> Entering any area consecrated to Nhimbaloth, or during the initial @JournalEntry[Abomination Vaults#Belcorra Attacks]{Belcorra Attacks!} encounter</p></section><section class=\"traits\"><p><strong>Curse | Auditory | Illusion | Magical | Mental | Visual</strong></p></section><p><strong>Your Lot, To Die</strong><br />So close to the unspeakable horror of Nhimbaloth's realm, you can no longer distinguish friend from foe, reason from madness, or even life from death.</p><hr /><section class=\"statblock\"><p><strong>Stage 1 </strong>You are @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.HL2l2VRSaQHu9lUw]{Fatigued}. At the start of your first turn in combat, you take @Damage[(4d6)[slashing]]{4d6 slashing damage} that cannot be prevented in any way. Also, whenever you take slashing damage, you must succeed at the curse save or become @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.e1XGnhKNSQIm5IXg]{Stupefied 1}. (1 day)</p><p><strong>Stage 2 </strong>You are @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.HL2l2VRSaQHu9lUw]{Fatigued}. At the start of your first turn in combat, you take @Damage[(6d6)[slashing]]{6d6 slashing damage} that cannot be prevented in any way. Also, whenever you take slashing damage, you must succeed at the curse save or become @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.e1XGnhKNSQIm5IXg]{Stupefied 2}. (1 day)</p><p><strong>Stage 3 </strong>You are @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.HL2l2VRSaQHu9lUw]{Fatigued}. At the start of your first turn in combat, you take @Damage[(8d6)[slashing]]{8d6 slashing damage} that cannot be prevented in any way. Also, whenever you take slashing damage, you must succeed at the curse save or become @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.e1XGnhKNSQIm5IXg]{Stupefied 4}. (1 day)</p><p><strong>Stage 4 </strong>You die, and your spirit is consumed by the Empty Death.</p></section>"
    },
